v0.9.9b (2024-01-30)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.9

v0.9.8b (2023-09-29)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.7

v0.9.7b (2023-09-04)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.6
 * Corrected default charset used by TeXParser

v0.9.6b (2023-08-24)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.5
 * Added \LaTeXe and \two@digits
 * Added extra debugging
 * added TeXApp.getDefaultCharset()

v0.9.5b (2023-04-24)

 * Bundled bib2gls v3.3
 * Added \text and TeXMode
 * Improved MathJax support
 * Added SingleToken
 * Added case-change support for eszett etc
 * Added toTruncatedString for lists to provide abridged output

v0.9.2.9b (2022-11-24)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.2
 * Added option in AuxParser to determine whether or not known catcode 
   changing commands should implement the category code change or 
   ignore their argument.

v0.9.2.8b (2022-11-05)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.1
 * Added limited support for \NewDocumentCommand, \RenewDocumentCommand,
   \ProvideDocumentCommand and \DeclareDocumentCommand. 
   (Some argument specifiers not recognised.)

v0.9.2.7b (2022-10-15)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v3.0
 * Limited support for twemojis and fontawesome.
 * Limited implementation of glossaries (not used by bib2gls, 
   which has the data stored in a subclass of BibEntry). 
   This is essentially limited to the feature set required by nlctuserguide.sty.
 * Implementation of nlctuserguide.sty

v0.9.2.6b (2021-11-25)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.8 and v2.9
 * Implemented \MFUskippunc and \MFUwordbreak in mfirstuc.

v0.9.2.5b (2020-07-11)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.7
 * Bug fixes in SI units.

v0.9.2.4b (2020-05-30)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.5
 * Bug fix: corrected \else part of conditionals.

v0.9.2.3b (2020-05-27)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.4
 * Fixed bug #3: If.doTruePart results in infinite loop on encountering begin group

v0.9.2.2b (2020-03-23)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.3

v0.9.2b (2020-03-16)

 * Corrected check for root directory

v0.9.1b (2020-02-28)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.1
 * Include parser when throwing TeXSyntaxException
 * Extended permitted commands allowed in aux parser

v0.9b (2020-02-12)

 * Bundled with bib2gls v2.0
 * Added commands for (re)defining robust commands

v0.8b (2019-12-14)

 * This release is the first version to use the new naming scheme 
   "auxfile" instead of "aux" (see issue #1) and "test" instead of "app".

v0.7b Legacy (2019-12-14)

 * This is the last release to include the "aux" folder. This will be 
   renamed in future versions to allow the repository to be cloned 
   under Windows. (See issue #1.) Any existing code will need to be 
   modified for future versions. (This includes bib2gls.)

v0.1b (2013-10-06)

 * Migrated from local subversion repository to GitHub.
